Pull request opened: https://github.com/graphql-python/graphene-sqlalchemy/pull/87.

```python
class ReporterType(SQLAlchemyObjectType):
    class Meta:
        model = Reporter

class Mutation(graphene.ObjectType):
    createReporter = create(ReporterType)

query = '''
    mutation createReporter{
        createReporter (firstName: "ABC", lastName: "def") {
            firstName,
            lastName,
            email
        }
    }
'''

schema = graphene.Schema(mutation=Mutation)
# SQLAlchemy session must be given to context for mutations.
result = schema.execute(query, context_value={'session': session})
```

it's implemented with Mutation subclass types defined in [mutation.py](https://github.com/Toilal/graphene-sqlalchemy/blob/894517dac26eb2b39319d6bceeabaa478dcba61c/graphene_sqlalchemy/mutations.py)

