@zballs the condition format hasn't changed; the beginning of the fulfillment URI is the same as the condition URI (note that both are just hashes of the Ed25519 public key).

I recently had to double-check my work on [creating transactions in JavaScript](https://github.com/sohkai/js-bigchaindb-quickstart) to make sure things were matching up with what the server expects, so I can try to help a bit here. Something that might help with the investigation is the public/private keypairs that you're using (or throwaway ones, if sensitive) either as base58 strings, or some representation in binary, to let us re-create and re-sign the same transaction to see what we get.

Do note that [there are a few gotchas](https://github.com/sohkai/js-bigchaindb-quickstart#rotating_light-warning-warning-warning-rotating_light) that you might also want to double check your implementations against.

