I think an informative error is quite doable:
```c++
// the unified char caster with potential silent failure for a single char
operator CharT&() { return value[0]; }
```
```c++
// unified caster with loud failure
operator CharT&() { 
    if (value.size() == 1)
        return value[0]; 
    else
        throw InformativeError();
}
````

