@mlindner as I understand your request that bash script does what you wanted, obviously you'd need to add any extra mpv options. 

I don't this the feature can be implemented in a user friendly enough way to be added as a core feature, and is better implemented with an external script. There are too many edge/failure cases. Tell me what you would expect the behaviour to be if you supplied a playlist with 10 hls streams and 1 hds stream at the end? 

Additionally, Streamlink is mainly aimed at live streaming, which don't really need to be played back to back.
